Responsible Changed
From-To: timur->rwatson

Robert, can you please take a look onto this PR? Logically, and 
comparing with Linux implementation, changes to ACLs shouldn't affect 
mtime, as file data doesn't change, only inode info(hence ctime is 
affected). 

Thanks, Timur. 

#include <sys/types.h>
#include <sys/stat.h>
#include <sys/extattr.h>
#include <sys/uio.h>

int main() {
char *file="test.txt";
char buf[512];
struct stat sb;

stat(file, &sb);
printf("Mtime: %ld, Ctime: %ld\n", sb.st_mtime, sb.st_ctime);
extattr_get_file(file, EXTATTR_NAMESPACE_USER, "dosattr", (void*)&buf, sizeof(buf));
stat(file, &sb);
printf("Mtime: %ld, Ctime: %ld\n", sb.st_mtime, sb.st_ctime);
memcpy(buf, "1234567890", 10);
extattr_set_file(file, EXTATTR_NAMESPACE_USER, "dosattr", (void*)&buf, sizeof(buf));
stat(file, &sb);
printf("Mtime: %ld, Ctime: %ld\n", sb.st_mtime, sb.st_ctime);
extattr_get_file(file, EXTATTR_NAMESPACE_USER, "dosattr", (void*)&buf, sizeof(buf));
stat(file, &sb);
printf("Mtime: %ld, Ctime: %ld\n", sb.st_mtime, sb.st_ctime);
}
